(Real Learning Application) Tj
T*
(In real study situations, students master Equilibrium by practising with tasks that) Tj
T*
(mirror Le Chatelier style reasoning. The topic becomes more meaningful when it is linked) Tj
T*
(to examples, revision drills, and exam-style questions that reflect how Chemistry is) Tj
T*
(assessed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on explaining what happens when concentration changes.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in dynamic balance and factors that shift equilibrium that) Tj
T*
(the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Equilibrium step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on Le Chatelier style reasoning.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid thinking equilibrium means the reaction has stopped while) Tj
T*
(solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Equilibrium: dynamic balance and factors that shift) Tj
T*
(equilibrium.) Tj
T*
(- Thinking equilibrium means the reaction has stopped.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Equilibrium without checking whether the method matches the question being) Tj
T*
(asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Study Tips) Tj
T*
(- Rewrite the overview of Equilibrium in your own words after studying it.) Tj
T*
(- Use short exercises built around Le Chatelier style reasoning before trying harder) Tj
T*
(tasks.) Tj
T*
(- Keep track of mistakes such as thinking equilibrium means the reaction has stopped and) Tj
T*
(write the correction beside each one.) Tj
T*
(- Revise Equilibrium regularly so the method behind dynamic balance and factors that) Tj
T*
(shift equilibrium becomes familiar.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Practice Exercises) Tj
T*
